  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Investment Broker",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Trade Execution:</strong> Execute buy and sell orders for securities on behalf of clients or firms.</li><li><strong>Portfolio Management:</strong> Review, monitor, and update client investment portfolios to align with financial goals and risk tolerance.</li><li><strong>Market Analysis:</strong> Analyze financial markets, economic data, and company research to identify investment opportunities.</li><li><strong>Client Relations:</strong> Advise clients on investment strategies, provide updates, and build trust-based relationships.</li><li><strong>Business Development:</strong> Source new clients through networking, prospecting, and cold calling.</li><li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Ensure all activities adhere to industry regulations (e.g., FINRA). </li></ul><p><strong>Required Skills and Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Education:</strong> Bachelor's degree in Finance, Accounting, Economics, or related fields.</li><li><strong>Licensing:</strong> Relevant industry licenses (e.g., Series 7, Series 63, or equivalent).</li><li><strong>Analytical Skills:</strong> Strong ability to interpret financial data and market trends.</li><li><strong>Communication:</strong> Excellent communication skills for client presentations and advising.</li><li><strong>Software Proficiency:</strong> Experience with trading platforms and Microsoft Office (Excel). </li></ul>",
